author: jerenkrantz
msg: ra_serf: Support fetch-props tag in update-report response so that we don't
have to do the PROPFIND when only the directory or file contents changed.
* subversion/libsvn_ra_serf/update.c
(report_dir_t): Add fetch_props and tag_closed fields.
(report_fetch_t): Add fetch_props field.
(fetch_file): Only perform PROPFINDs if we've been told to fetch them (or
we're adding a file).
(start_report): Init fetch_props to false when opening a file/dir and true
when adding a file/dir or opening the root; if we see the fetch-props tag in
the report, ensure we will fetch the properties.
(end_report): Set a flag when we're done with the dir tag and only fetch the
directory properties when we've been told to do so; add some protection for
closing the open-file and add-file tags.
(finish_report): Simplify the cleanup of directories and account for the
fact that not all dirs will be fetching properties.
* subversion/libsvn_ra_serf/property.c
(walk_all_props): Exit early if we don't have any properties for this path.

author: jerenkrantz
msg: ra_serf: Fix up a pool life-time issue with the root dir; always ensure that
we open/close the root dir even if there are no files; avoid some needless
NULLs.
* subversion/libsvn_ra_serf/update.c
(push_state): Avoid some needless updates (these structures are pcalloc'd)
(open_dir): Pass ->dir_baton_pool to open_root call instead of ->pool.
(finish_report): Note if we closed our root and if we haven't, always
close it at the very end.
